00:47:05.400 --> 00:47:07.300
Microsoft SQL, these types of data warehouses,

00:47:08.220 --> 00:47:11.380
generally you're trying to model some type of business process.

00:47:12.240 --> 00:47:14.720
And typically people use SQL to do that.

00:47:15.740 --> 00:47:17.600
Now you can do this without dbt,

00:47:17.900 --> 00:47:21.480
but dbt has provided a nice clean interface to doing so.

00:47:22.080 --> 00:47:23.900
It makes it very easy to connect these models together,

00:47:24.120 --> 00:47:27.780
to run them, to have a development workflow that works really well.

00:47:28.120 --> 00:47:30.920
And then you can push it to prod and have things run again in production.

00:47:31.180 --> 00:47:32.500
So that's dbt.

00:47:33.800 --> 00:47:35.000
We find it works really well.

00:47:35.440 --> 00:47:37.940
And a lot of our customers are actually using dbt as well.

